gr.forth.ics.swkm.model2
Interface RdfNode

All Known Subinterfaces:
BlankNode, ClassView, ContainerView, IndividualView, Inheritable, LiteralNode, MetaclassView, MetapropertyView, ObjectNode, PropertyView, Resource, View
public interface RdfNode

A representation of an RDF entity (a Resource, a BlankNode, or a LiteralNode). An RdfNode is created by Model and can at most be owned by a single Model.

Nodes have an associated type (see type(). This is automatically inferred by the owner model, using RDF inference rules. See "Discussion on the semantics of rdfs:Resource, rdfs:Class, rdf:Property" for a reference of these rules. The type of a node may change during its lifetime, due to triple additions/deletions. It should be noted that, for uniformity, literal nodes also have a type, which is always RdfType.LITERAL. Notice that typing information of a model can only produce contradictions when adding triples. In such a case, an RdfTypeException will be thrown, and any changed types will be reverted to the last valid values.

An RdfNode can offer more methods based on its type. For example, if node.type().isClass(), then the node can be viewed as a class. In particular, ClassView classView = node.asClass(); would access the ClassView interface that offers specialized methods for nodes that are classes. Similar interfaces exist for other types (properties, metaclasses, metaproperties, individuals, named graphs), see the asXXX methods and the gr.forth.ics.swkm.model2.views package.

Author:
Andreou Dimitris, email: jim.andreou (at) gmail (dot) com
See Also:
"Discussion on the semantics of rdfs:Resource, rdfs:Class, rdf:Property" for a reference of supported RDF typing rules.

subjectTriples

Triples subjectTriples()
Returns the triples that have this node as subject, in the model that owns this node. If this node is not an ObjectNode (or equivalently isObjectNode() returns false) then this method is guaranteed to return no results, since only ObjectNodes can ever be the subject of a triple.

Returns:
the triples that have this node as subject, in the model that owns this node

mappedTo

RdfNode mappedTo(Model model)

asInheritable

Inheritable asInheritable()
                          throws IllegalStateException
Returns an inheritable (that is "something that can be part of an inheritance relationship") view of this node. The returned view is only usable as long as this node remains an inheritable, or else its methods will throw an IllegalStateException. For convenience, this call succeeds even for XML types, although these do not participate in any inheritance relationship.

Returns:
a named graph view of this node
Throws:
IllegalStateException - if type() != RdfType.CLASS && type() != RdfType.PROPERTY && type() != RdfType.METACLASS && type() != RdfType.METAPROPERTY && type() != RdfType.XML_TYPE
